Reasoning: The paper deals with mathematical structures and their applications in molecular evolution. The concepts of cographs, di-cographs, and hierarchical structures are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of symbolic ultrametrics and the characterization of relation structures suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the study of ancestral events and types of gene duplication and transfer may also be relevant to computational biology (cs.GT).
